article.headline: Murray St. 72, Jacksonville St. 71 OT
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Kevin Thomas' free throw with six seconds left in overtime lifted Murray State to a 72-71 victory over Jacksonville State Tuesday night. Jacksonville State (3-7, 1-3 Ohio Valley Conference) sent the game into overtime when Dorien Brown hit a layup to make the score 62-62 with seven seconds remaining in regulation. Bruce Carter scored seven points in overtime for Murray (5-7, 3-1), including two crucial free throws to give the Racers a 71-68 lead. But a 3-pointer by Nick Smith with 14 seconds left tied the game again at 71. Thomas was fouled on Murray's next possession and connected on one shot. Jacksonville State took control of the ball with six seconds left, but a Tracy Thomas layup attempt fell short. The score was also tied at halftime, 31-31. Carter and Ed Horton scored 16 points apiece for Murray, while Danero Thomas and Kevin Thomas had 12 points each. Jacksonville State had three players with double-doubles. Courtney Bradley had 22 points and 14 rebounds, Dorien Brown had 21 points and 10 rebounds and Erik Adams finished with 10 points and 12 boards.
